Dear ALF III Investor,
We're proud to share that Viola Credit has successfully completed the final=
 close of the third series of Asset-Based Lending funds, ALF III (the "Fund=
"). The Fund raised over $2.0 billion of committed and investable capital (=
including related vehicles). This surpasses our original $1.5 billion targe=
t.
We're honored to receive the continued trust of our longstanding partners, =
while also being greatly appreciative of the trust placed in us by our new =
LPs. The Fund received commitments from a wide range of global investors, i=
ncluding leading pension funds, insurance companies, financial institutions=
, investment consultants, and global advisors. We believe this speaks to th=
e value that our differentiated approach to asset-based lending within the =
innovation economy can bring to our LPs.
As the ABL landscape continues to evolve, we believe ALF III will see a sig=
nificant number of opportunities to partner with best-in-class FinTech and =
tech-enabled lenders.  We will seek to support these originators as they ex=
pand, diversify their funding base, and give them access to scalable capita=
l solutions.
We would like to take this opportunity to also welcome Conor Sheehy to the =
Firm as the Head of ABL Europe, based in our London office. Conor brings ov=
er 20 years of experience in structured finance and warehouse lending, most=
 recently leading the European Warehouse Finance business at HSBC Innovatio=
n Bank. Conor joins our established and growing global platform of over 40 =
professionals across Viola Credit.
We wanted to thank you for your trust and ongoing partnership. We remain co=
mmitted to delivering disciplined returns and long-term value to you, our v=
alued partners.
Warm regards,
Ido Vigdor, Ruthi Furman, Alex Ginzburg
On behalf of the entire
Viola Credit Management Team

